<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="555" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d555">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.001M52/28</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Cuban Minister</gloss> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 60</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Cuban Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-21">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 21, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have the honor to inform your
                            excellency that on yesterday the 20th of May 1917, Messrs. Mario G.
                            Menocal and Emilio Nuñez assumed the offices of President and Vice
                            President of the Republic of Cuba to which they were respectively
                            proclaimed by the National Congress to have been elected for the term of
                            four years which will end on May 21, 1921.</p>
                        <p>I avail [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Carlos Manuel de Céspedes</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>